      "message": "[Critical] Line 1884: Calling `fallbackClone({}, convId)` after rejecting the corrupted repository can fail to find peers because the active `Conversation` was deliberately not published, and an empty sender gives the clone path no known source device to target. In that case recovery becomes a no-op even though `convInfos_` still has member metadata. Build the source list from the stored metadata before scheduling the clone, or add an overload that re-clones from `convInfos_` explicitly.\n\n```suggestion\nfor (const auto\u0026 convId : toReclone) {\n    const auto members \u003d shared-\u003econversationMembersFromInfos(convId);\n    shared-\u003efallbackClone(members, convId);\n}\n```",
