      "message": "Line 2341: The test ignores the return value from `makeGitObjectUnreachable()`. If the HEAD object is packed, the helper may remove the whole pack directory and still return false, which makes the test less precise and can hide that it did not corrupt exactly the object the scenario describes. Assert the return value here, as the repository tests do.\n\n```suggestion\nCPPUNIT_ASSERT(makeGitObjectUnreachable(repoPath / \".git\" / \"objects\", head));\n```",
